        <title>Google Analytics 500 Server Error</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[juanma]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/justin">@justin</a></p>
<p>Can you please <strong><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/about-the-dev-talk-questions-category/2/3">provide a repo or code-sandbox with your code</a></strong>? This is especially helpful to find solutions of technical issues with specific code</p>
<p>Have you checked the <a href="https://api.frontity.org/frontity-packages/features-packages/analytics">documentation of the Analytics Packages</a>?</p>
<p>That setting is enough to start tracking your pageviews (the tracking will be done automatically by default if this setting is detected).</p>
<p><a href="https://api.frontity.org/frontity-packages/features-packages/analytics#actions-analytics-pageview"><code>actions.analytics.pageview</code></a> is not meant to be called manually. Maybe you’r calling it without any argument?</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/google-analytics-500-server-error/4108/3">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
